<i>But he did not appreciate that Morris
Brandt had kept the pills for himself.</i>

01:32:25.541 --> 01:32:27.876
<i>And it was all still possible.</i>

01:32:46.353 --> 01:32:48.856
Actually, no, there's no more tickets.

01:32:48.939 --> 01:32:53.402
Yeah, I know. An overbooked fundraiser.
That's a first.

01:32:53.485 --> 01:32:55.154
Well, here he comes. I'll ask him.

01:32:55.904 --> 01:32:57.322
Oh, that's much better.

01:32:57.406 --> 01:32:59.950
- Great job.
- Thank you, sir.

01:33:00.034 --> 01:33:01.160
Hi, Mr. Morra.

01:33:01.243 --> 01:33:03.078
Edward!

01:33:04.455 --> 01:33:06.707
I think we're looking
at a second overflow event.

01:33:06.790 --> 01:33:08.792
There's a wave of donations coming in
and I don't think

01:33:08.876 --> 01:33:11.170
they're even gonna
try a second debate.

01:33:11.253 --> 01:33:12.504
- Great.
- Hold on.

01:33:12.588 --> 01:33:14.214
A guy from
Eiben-Chemcorp's in your office.

01:33:14.298 --> 01:33:16.050
- I have a lunch.
- They're your biggest contributor.

01:33:16.133 --> 01:33:17.342
Give him his two crappy little minutes.

01:33:17.426 --> 01:33:19.803
- Eiben-Chemcorp Pharmaceuticals?
- Yeah.

01:33:21.680 --> 01:33:24.391
Finally get to meet the guys
that keep the lights on.

01:33:25.893 --> 01:33:27.686
- Carl!
- Mr. Morra.

01:33:29.146 --> 01:33:32.649
What a surprise. They told me somebody
from Eiben was coming.

01:33:32.733 --> 01:33:36.070
Chemcorp. Yeah, that's me now. I'm
moving out of the energy business.

01:33:36.153 --> 01:33:39.865
Come on. That's like Hef
moving out of the mansion.

01:33:39.948 --> 01:33:43.202
Yeah. I bought Eiben a couple of months
ago. I'm surprised you didn't hear.

01:33:43.285 --> 01:33:47.331
No. No. Well, they really
keep me hopping here.

01:33:47.414 --> 01:33:50.209
Well, it's gonna pay off,
Senator Morra.

01:33:51.543 --> 01:33:53.921
The Senate. Who knows...

01:33:54.004 --> 01:33:57.341
Everything's a technicality
from here on in, isn't it, Eddie?

01:33:58.008 --> 01:34:02.596
I think we both know where it's headed,
if you can maintain.

01:34:05.432 --> 01:34:08.644
Have you asked yourself what
you're gonna do when you run out?

01:34:24.326 --> 01:34:27.329
- When did you know?
- Does it matter? I know now.

01:34:28.413 --> 01:34:31.834
I wish you'd come to me at first, Eddie.
I could have bought Eiben at 33 a share.

01:34:31.917 --> 01:34:33.335
We could have been partners.

01:34:37.089 --> 01:34:38.924
So, Eiben makes NZT.

01:34:39.007 --> 01:34:41.802
Well, it'll never officially exist.

01:34:41.885 --> 01:34:44.429
Obviously, I don't need
to point out the advantages for you.

01:34:45.347 --> 01:34:46.849
Oh, I think maybe you do.

01:34:46.932 --> 01:34:50.853
Limitless supply.
We know you can't get any more.

01:34:50.936 --> 01:34:52.437
You sure about that?

01:34:52.521 --> 01:34:54.356
They shut down your lab this morning.

01:34:56.859 --> 01:35:00.404
Eddie. I just want to help you,
that's all.

01:35:00.487 --> 01:35:03.448
Keep you supplied.
No disruption in service.

01:35:03.532 --> 01:35:05.617
Give you peace of mind.
That's all.

01:35:07.286 --> 01:35:10.289
And in return, I do what?

01:35:10.372 --> 01:35:14.168
Get a little advice, maybe.
I won't be bothering you much at first.

01:35:14.251 --> 01:35:16.712
And later. What are you
gonna be bothering me with?

01:35:16.795 --> 01:35:20.465
Well, given where you're heading,
some of our ideas are a bit ambitious.

01:35:20.549 --> 01:35:22.426
But hey, I think they're achievable.

01:35:22.509 --> 01:35:24.261
And what if I don't like your ideas?

01:35:24.344 --> 01:35:26.722
Then we'll say, "Godspeed."

01:35:26.805 --> 01:35:30.309
And your candle will have shed a brief,
but lovely light.

01:35:32.186 --> 01:35:33.645
But you know what, Eddie,
let's not even

01:35:33.729 --> 01:35:34.730
go there right now.

01:35:34.813 --> 01:35:38.108
Right now, I just want
to keep you brilliant...

01:35:38.192 --> 01:35:41.904
...and healthy. Come on.
Let's go get some lunch.

01:36:00.172 --> 01:36:02.132
After you, Senator.

01:36:03.675 --> 01:36:05.594
Thanks for stopping by, Carl.

01:36:06.470 --> 01:36:08.222
Give us a second.

01:36:08.305 --> 01:36:11.016
What are you doing? Do you want
to be President of the United States

01:36:11.099 --> 01:36:13.769
- or brain dead, stuck full of tubes?
- I'll take my chances.

01:36:13.852 --> 01:36:17.064
I told you your chances don't exist.
We shut down your lab.

01:36:17.147 --> 01:36:18.357
You don't think some smartass on NZT

01:36:18.440 --> 01:36:20.025
might have two or three
or even four labs?

01:36:20.108 --> 01:36:22.277
- So what? You're not making any more.
- That's right, I'm not.

01:36:22.361 --> 01:36:24.404
I thought better of it.
See, once you know what's in it,

01:36:24.488 --> 01:36:28.116
you can tweak it, re-engineer it.
Get the bugs out. Taper off.

01:36:28.825 --> 01:36:30.160
I'm off it, Carl.

01:36:30.244 --> 01:36:31.495
Well, on it or off it,

01:36:31.578 --> 01:36:33.872
there's no scenario
where you're not working for me.

01:36:33.956 --> 01:36:35.457
How you gonna pay me?
In cigarettes?

01:36:35.540 --> 01:36:36.708
Last year you traded

01:36:36.792 --> 01:36:38.710
- inside information 17 times.
- You threatening me?

01:36:38.794 --> 01:36:41.880
Blank checks from Dubai.
Dumping in Chile. Disappeared officials.

01:36:41.964 --> 01:36:44.049
- I mean, you shed a spot light...
- Do you want to go to war with me?

01:36:44.132 --> 01:36:46.218
And trust me when I say this,
I'm not even being creative.

01:36:46.301 --> 01:36:48.262
There's no way you can be making
accusations like that

01:36:48.345 --> 01:36:50.681
and be walking around alive.

01:36:50.764 --> 01:36:53.350
That you would even think that shows me
how unprepared you are to fight me.

01:36:53.433 --> 01:36:54.977
- You're no longer equipped to fight me.
- I may be off it,

01:36:55.060 --> 01:36:57.437
but you think I didn't learn anything?
That my synapses didn't change?

01:36:57.521 --> 01:36:58.855
That I kept absolutely nothing?

01:36:58.939 --> 01:37:00.524
You have no idea what
kind of enemy I can be.

01:37:00.607 --> 01:37:03.443
- That van's gonna rear-end that taxi.
- What?

01:37:03.527 --> 01:37:06.196
The driver's distracted. He's texting.
He's going 30 miles an hour.

01:37:06.280 --> 01:37:08.073
He has 60 feet to stop.
He doesn't have room.

01:37:08.156 --> 01:37:09.908
- What van?

01:37:13.245 --> 01:37:14.621
I see everything, Carl.

01:37:14.705 --> 01:37:16.999
I'm 50 moves ahead of you
and everybody else.

01:37:17.082 --> 01:37:19.418
What makes you think I don't have a guy
with a bead on you right now?

01:37:19.501 --> 01:37:21.211
How do you know you're gonna be alive
this time next year?

01:37:21.295 --> 01:37:24.423
What are you doing? You get
your hands off me. What are you doing?

01:37:24.506 --> 01:37:27.259
Something's pumping half-mass in there.
The walls of your heart are dilated.

01:37:27.342 --> 01:37:30.554
Your aortic valve's steno. So you're
gonna need to get that replaced.

01:37:32.347 --> 01:37:33.974
But you already knew that.

01:37:39.771 --> 01:37:41.606
You know, you should
really be glad about this.

01:37:41.690 --> 01:37:44.735
'Cause me working for you?
You'd end up as my bitch.

01:37:56.705 --> 01:37:59.458
Maybe we should cool off.
Talk again.

01:38:01.293 --> 01:38:03.170
I don't think so.

01:38:04.755 --> 01:38:06.006
Don't forget to vote.

01:38:14.306 --> 01:38:15.724
Edward.

01:38:15.807 --> 01:38:17.434
You good?

01:38:17.517 --> 01:38:20.479
Yeah. Told you I have a lunch.

01:38:26.401 --> 01:38:28.779
- Sorry I'm late.
- Hey. Don't worry.

01:38:30.864 --> 01:38:33.408
- How's your day going?
- Ah. I've had better.

01:38:35.243 --> 01:38:37.245
I still can't deal with that haircut.

01:38:37.329 --> 01:38:39.414
I wouldn't even
recognize you on the street.

01:38:39.498 --> 01:38:41.249
Well, I'm a new man.

01:38:42.584 --> 01:38:43.585
I've already ordered.

01:38:59.518 --> 01:39:01.103
What?

